Rewterz Threat Alert BlackMoon Banking Trojan Active IOCs
text: BlackMoon, aka KRBanker, is a banking trojan it can steal financial and banking account information as well as other sensitive data. Blackmoon was discovered in 2014 by Fortinet researchers, and it is back again with a new campaign. Blackmoon used to attack the host with URLs, advertisements, and other web content. Once the host has been compromised it can open multiple pop-ups.
